<title>USA: Ceridian says 1997 expectations unchanged.</title>
<headline>Ceridian says 1997 expectations unchanged.</headline>
<dateline>MINNEAPOLIS 1997-07-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ceridian Corp said 1997 earnings expectations have not changed, although its Comdata gaming operation is feeling competitive pressures that could reduce growth in the gaming business for the rest of the year.</p>
<p>The information services and defense electronics company reported second quarter 1997 net earnings of $48.5 million on revenue of $404.2 million. Second quarter 1996 earnings were $40.8 million on revenue of $361.5 million.</p>
<p>&quot;All of Ceridian's businesses performed as expected in the second quarter,&quot; said chief executive Lawrence Perlman.</p>
<p>((--Chicago Newsdesk 312-408-8787))</p>
